  "description": "Weapons progression from stone blades through bronze swords, iron-age weapons, steel swords and polearms, to black powder firearms (matchlock, flintlock, percussion cap). Blade hardness requirements: stone (Mohs 5-7), bronze (HB 80-120), wrought iron (HB 90-120), medium-carbon steel (HRC 45-55 for swords, HRC 58-62 for knife edges). Musket bore: 17.5-19 mm (.69-.75 caliber). Cross-reference chemistry/explosives.md for propellant compositions.",
